</exercise>
</note><para id="fs-idm66602256">Archaean cell walls do not have peptidoglycan. There are four different types of Archaean cell walls. One type is composed of <emphasis>pseudopeptidoglycan</emphasis>, which is similar to peptidoglycan in morphology but contains different sugars in the polysaccharide chain. The other three types of cell walls are composed of polysaccharides, glycoproteins, or pure protein.</para>
