<para id="fs-id1167065877121">Students should identify similarities between prokaryotes and eukaryotes such as the use of DNA, ribosomes, and ATP. Prokaryotes and eukaryotes are different in that prokaryotes do not have membrane-bound organelles such as mitochondria and nuclei. Both questions above are applications of AP<sup>®</sup> Learning Objective 2.14 and Science Practice 1.4 because students are asked to describe differences and similarities in prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells in addition to differences between bacteria and archaea.</para>
</note>
